    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/adjoint-pair/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/adjoint-pair/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;An adjoint pair (or adjunction) is a pair of &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functors&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F: C \to D&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;G: D \to C&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; between &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;categories&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;C&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;D&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, connected by a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/natural-transformation/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;natural&lt;/a&gt; bijection:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34; display=&#34;block&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;m&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;≅&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;m&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{Hom}_D(F(a), b) \cong \mathrm{Hom}_C(a, G(b))&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;for all objects &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;a&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;C&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;b&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;D&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the &lt;strong&gt;left adjoint&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the &lt;strong&gt;right adjoint&lt;/strong&gt;, written &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⊣&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F \dashv G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The left adjoint is &amp;ldquo;free&amp;rdquo; — it generates structure. The right adjoint is &amp;ldquo;forgetful&amp;rdquo; — it constrains or tests. The adjunction says: a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphism&lt;/a&gt; out of the free construction &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F(a)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; corresponds exactly to a morphism into the forgetful image &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;G(b)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/hyperdoctrine/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/hyperdoctrine/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A hyperdoctrine (Lawvere 1969, 1970) is a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functor&lt;/a&gt; from a base &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt; of contexts to a fiber category of propositions:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34; display=&#34;block&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;P&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;script&#34;&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;bold&#34;&gt;L&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;bold&#34;&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;bold&#34;&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;P: \mathcal{C}^{\mathrm{op}} \to \mathbf{Lat}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;For each context &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;c&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;script&#34;&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathcal{C}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the fiber &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;P&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;P(c)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a lattice of propositions that can be stated in context &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;c&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. For each morphism &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f: c \to d&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (a substitution or change of context), the reindexing map &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;P&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;P&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;P&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;P(f): P(d) \to P(c)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; pulls back propositions from context &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;d&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; to context &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;c&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The reindexing maps have &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/adjoint-pair/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;adjoint pairs&lt;/a&gt;: left adjoints &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;∃&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\exists_f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (existential quantification along &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) and right adjoints &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;∀&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\forall_f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; (universal quantification along &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Kan Extension</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/kan-extension/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/kan-extension/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A Kan extension is the universal way to extend a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functor&lt;/a&gt; along another &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functor&lt;/a&gt;. Given &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functors&lt;/a&gt; F: C → D and K: C → E, the left Kan extension Lan_K(F): E → D is the &amp;ldquo;best approximation&amp;rdquo; of F that factors through K.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The left Kan extension Lan_K(F) is characterized by a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/natural-transformation/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;natural transformation&lt;/a&gt; η: F ⇒ Lan_K(F) ∘ K that is universal: for any other &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functor&lt;/a&gt; G: E → D with a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/natural-transformation/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;natural transformation&lt;/a&gt; F ⇒ G ∘ K, there is a unique &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/natural-transformation/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;natural transformation&lt;/a&gt; Lan_K(F) ⇒ G making everything commute. The right Kan extension Ran_K(F) satisfies the dual universal &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/terms/property/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;property&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A category C consists of a collection of &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;objects&lt;/a&gt;, a collection of &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphisms&lt;/a&gt; between objects, and a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/composition/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;composition&lt;/a&gt; operation satisfying two laws.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For every pair of objects A and B, there is a collection Hom(A, B) of morphisms from A to B. For every composable pair &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f : A \to B&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g : B \to C&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, there is a composite &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g \circ f : A \to C&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. For every object A, there is an &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/identity-morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;identity morphism&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{id}_A : A \to A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. These satisfy:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A functor &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F : C \to D&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a map from one &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt; to another that preserves the structure. It sends &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;objects&lt;/a&gt; to objects and &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphisms&lt;/a&gt; to morphisms. It does not break &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/composition/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;composition&lt;/a&gt; or identities: if &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; compose to &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;h&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in C, then &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F(f)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F(g)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; compose to &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F(h)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in D. If &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{id}_A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is an &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/identity-morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;identity morphism&lt;/a&gt;, then &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F(\mathrm{id}_A) = \mathrm{id}_{F(A)}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;That is the whole definition. A functor maps things and arrows between things, and it respects how arrows chain together. A functor is to categories what a homomorphism is to groups or a continuous map is to topological spaces — a structure-preserving translation between structured worlds.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/identity-morphism/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/identity-morphism/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The identity morphism &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{id}_A : A \to A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphism&lt;/a&gt; on an &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;object&lt;/a&gt; A that acts as the neutral element for &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/composition/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;composition&lt;/a&gt;. Composing with the identity before or after any morphism leaves it unchanged:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34; display=&#34;block&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mspace width=&#34;2em&#34;/&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f \circ \mathrm{id}_A = f \qquad \mathrm{id}_B \circ f = f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;for every morphism &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f : A \to B&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt; is required to have an identity morphism for every object. This is one of the two axioms of a category, alongside associativity of composition. Without identity morphisms, there would be no notion of &amp;ldquo;doing nothing&amp;rdquo; — no baseline against which other morphisms can be measured. The identity morphism is to composition what zero is to addition or one is to multiplication.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/isomorphism/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/isomorphism/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;An isomorphism is a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphism&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f : A \to B&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; that has a two-sided inverse: a morphism &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g : B \to A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; such that &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g \circ f = \mathrm{id}_A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f \circ g = \mathrm{id}_B&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. You can go there and come back and end up where you started, in both directions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Two &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;objects&lt;/a&gt; connected by an isomorphism are isomorphic. They are structurally identical from the perspective of the &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt;. Every property expressible in categorical terms is preserved by isomorphism. This makes isomorphism the correct notion of &amp;ldquo;sameness&amp;rdquo; in category theory: not literal equality of objects, but the existence of a structure-preserving correspondence that can be undone.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/natural-transformation/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/natural-transformation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A natural transformation &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⇒&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\alpha : F \Rightarrow G&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; between two &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/functor/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;functors&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;C&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;D&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F, G : C \to D&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; assigns to each &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;object&lt;/a&gt; c in C a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphism&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\alpha_c : F(c) \to G(c)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in D, such that for every morphism &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f : c \to c&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in C, the following square commutes:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34; display=&#34;block&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;G(f) \circ \alpha_c = \alpha_{c&amp;#x27;} \circ F(f)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;The commutativity condition is the substance of &amp;ldquo;natural.&amp;rdquo; It says that &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\alpha&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; does not depend on arbitrary choices. Transforming an object and then mapping it forward gives the same result as mapping it forward and then transforming it. The components &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;α&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\alpha_c&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; are coherent across the entire category — they fit together into a single, globally consistent mapping from F to G.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;An object is one of the two kinds of data in a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt; — the things that &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphisms&lt;/a&gt; go between.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What counts as an object depends on the category. In Set, objects are &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/sets/terms/set/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sets&lt;/a&gt;. In Top, objects are topological spaces. In a group G viewed as a one-object category, there is exactly one object (the group itself), and morphisms are the group elements. In a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/order/terms/partial-order/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;partial order&lt;/a&gt; viewed as a thin category, each element of the poset is an object.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Commutative Diagram</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/commutative-diagram/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/commutative-diagram/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A commutative diagram is a diagram of &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;objects&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphisms&lt;/a&gt; in which all directed paths between the same two objects compose to the same &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphism&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If a diagram contains two paths from A to C — say f: A → B followed by g: B → C, and also h: A → C directly — then the diagram commutes when g ∘ f = h. The visual layout encodes an equation: any two routes through the diagram that start and end at the same objects must give the same composite.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Composition</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/composition/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/composition/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Composition is the operation that combines two consecutive &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphisms&lt;/a&gt; into one. If f goes from A to B and g goes from B to C, their composite g ∘ f goes from A to C. You do f first, then g. The notation reads right to left: g ∘ f means &amp;ldquo;g after f.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Composition must follow two rules. First, associativity: if you have three morphisms in a row, it does not matter which pair you compose first. h ∘ (g ∘ f) = (h ∘ g) ∘ f. Second, the unit law: every &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;object&lt;/a&gt; has an &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/identity-morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;identity morphism&lt;/a&gt; that does nothing when composed with other morphisms. f ∘ id = f, and id ∘ g = g.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Morphism</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A morphism is a directed connection from one &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/object/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;object&lt;/a&gt; to another inside a &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt;. It extends a plain &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/terms/directed-graph/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;directed relation&lt;/a&gt; with the requirement that morphisms compose: if f goes from A to B and g goes from B to C, then there is a composite g ∘ f going from A to C, and this composition is associative.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every morphism has a source (where it starts) and a target (where it lands). Every object has an &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/math/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/identity-morphism/&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;identity morphism&lt;/a&gt; — an arrow from itself to itself that does nothing when composed with other arrows.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
